# LXDE Autostart file for Raspberry Pi kiosk mode
# Copy this file to: ~/.config/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart
# Then log out / log back in (or reboot) to auto-launch Chromium in kiosk mode.

# --- Wallboard Display (read-only roster) ---
# Uncomment ONE of these depending on your installed command:
# @chromium-browser --kiosk --check-for-update-interval=604800 --noerrdialogs --disable-translate --incognito http://localhost:5000/display
# @chromium --kiosk --check-for-update-interval=604800 --noerrdialogs --disable-translate --incognito http://localhost:5000/display

# --- Touchscreen Kiosk (sign-up form) ---
# Uncomment ONE of these depending on your installed command:
# @chromium-browser --kiosk --check-for-update-interval=604800 --noerrdialogs --disable-translate --incognito http://localhost:5000/
# @chromium --kiosk --check-for-update-interval=604800 --noerrdialogs --disable-translate --incognito http://localhost:5000/
